    "waves": 7,
    "hpMult": 1.53,
    "blurb": "Four monoliths ring a sunken reed island in a fog-drowned mire. Wade the causeways, relight what the water takes, and keep one light burning till dawn.",
    "newFeatures": [
      "Perimeter beacon ring",
      "Drowned-mire causeway routes",
      "Toxin-seeping peat & bog-spitters"
    ]
  },
  "intro": [
    {
      "title": "Drowned Circle",
      "lines": [
        "Four anchor monoliths ring the sunken basin, one to each quarter — the fog drowns the bridges between them.",
        "The mire rises and douses what you leave dark. Dark is not dead: wade out and relight by day.",
        "Bog-spitters foul the causeways and the peat itself seeps poison. Keep one light burning till the fifth dawn."
      ],
      "art": "siege"
    }
  ],
  "outro": [
    {
      "title": "The Circle Holds",
      "lines": [
        "Five dawns over the drowned basin, and at least one monolith never went black.",
        "The fog lifts off still water. The deep marches wait beyond the reeds."
      ],
      "art": "dawn"
    }
  ],
